<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEACH TRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Recently, volunteers gave up their valuable time to clean up all the trash on 
the local beaches. My point is, why should they do it? 
</P>
<P>
The real culprits are the slobs who leave their trash behind, without even so 
much as a second glance at the mess. I cannot understand why there isn't a 
stiff fine, or even a jail sentence for these people. They should be made to 
take all their own rubbish away, and if a trash container isn't handy, take it 
home and dispose of it on trash day. 
</P>
<P>
The beaches should be policed regularly, and if these people are guilty, ticket 
them, just like illegal parking or not using a seat belt. 
</P>
<P>
ELIZABETH C. MOSS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
