International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora, known as 
CITES, must find common ground between the East Africa demand for an ivory ban, 
supported by the United States and Western Europe, and the position that 
controlled marketing of tusks can finance anti-poaching measures. CITES rulings 
