Record early autumn cold penetrated the north-central part of the nation, while 
frost warnings were in place in Ohio, Indiana and Kentucky, where the National 
Weather Service expected that the first significant frost of the season could 
put an end to the growing season. The chill was blamed on a cold Canadian 
