<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAXIING JET HIT BY BOLT OF LIGHTNING; 1 KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORLANDO, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bolt of lightning struck a jetliner taxiing at Orlando International Airport, 
killing a ground-crew member who was helping guide it, officials said. No one 
aboard the plane was hurt. Witnesses reported seeing the bolt arc from the 
plane Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Skies were partly cloudy but there was no thunderstorm activity reported at the 
time. There was no apparent physical damage to the plane, a USAir spokeswoman 
said, but it was taken out of service for an inspection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
