WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
BRITISH SECURITY BLASTS ERRANT VAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BLACKPOOL, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Mexican trapeze artist today was the first victim of a massive security 
operation at the Conservative Party conference in Blackpool after his van was 
blown up by British troops. 
</P>
<P>
Gerardo Rodogel, late for his act at a circus Sunday night, left the 
Dutch-licensed van in a no-parking zone just yards from the site of the party's 
annual meeting in this northern English seaside resort. Minutes later police 
sealed off roads and called in army bomb disposal experts to carry out a 
"controlled explosion." 
</P>
<P>
Security has been very tight at Conservative Party conferences since their 1984 
meeting when a bomb planted by Irish republican guerrillas almost killed Prime 
Minister Margaret Thatcher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
