<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE CAUSES $1.5-MILLION IN DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire roared through a row of four businesses in South Gate early today, causing 
an estimated $1.5 million damage before it was controlled by 17 fire companies, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire in the complex in the 12000 block of South Garfield Avenue was 
reported at 4:46 a.m., Los Angeles County Fire Department dispatcher Lawrence 
Beals said. 
</P>
<P>
The firefighters battled the blaze for more than an hour before it was 
extinguished at 5:53 a.m., he said. 
</P>
<P>
Two firefighters suffered minor injuries, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the blaze was under investigation. 
</P>
