<P>
2 AIRLINERS IN TROUBLE LAND SAFELY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Pan Am 747 jetliner flying from New York to Madrid with 203 passengers aboard 
had engine problems, forcing the pilot to cut an engine and make an emergency 
landing in Gander, Newfoundland, Pan Am said today. 
</P>
<P>
The plane touched down smoothly and no one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Pan Am Flight 156, which left John F. Kennedy International Airport at 9:52 
p.m. Sunday after an hour and 42 minute delay, experienced vibration in one of 
its four engines off the coast of Canada just before midnight. The pilot cut 
the engine and turned back, Pan Am officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Also today, a Boeing 727 landed safely in Paris missing one wheel after losing 
part of its landing gear while taking off from Algiers. 
</P>
<P>
Orly airport officials said emergency services were put on alert, but Air 
Algeria Flight 1002 landed smoothly, and none of the 129 passengers aboard 
noticed anything amiss. 
</P>
</TEXT>
